Mission 23 hints:

- Start a new mission and build two or three barracks..
- Empty the buildings you have from the start for men..
- Set the barracks to produce 'full' soldiers..
- Sell iron/wood/stone/ore/coal for gold and armour until you have enough
  to turn all your pessants into soldiers..
- When you have app. 30 soldiers ready you head off, remember to take
  the knights with you, follow the coast along the bay going west and
  then south until you see a red gun-tower..
- Attack and take the guntower to protect the return trip, leave 2 or
  3 soldiers to guard and bring in some extra soldier from your base..
- If ANY guards approach you from other buildings then kill them at
  once, you might only get that one chance..
- Continue south to a red farmhouse, then a bit into the land you'll
  find the HQ. DON'T attack it, but put your soldiers outside and kill
  the guards approaching your men (Direct your people in the battle,
  send at least 4 soldiers on each enemy, more if the enemy is a 
  knight, to reduce your losses. DON'T count on the inteligence of
  your soldiers in battle)..
- (You might wanna call your last soldiers down to the enemy here, I
  didn't need to...)
- While the gurads are kept busy or dying, send some good (healthy)
  soldiers (I used the 6 knights) to the prisson and rescue your people.
- Gather all the people from the prisson with a few soldiers and GUIDE
  them to your HQ (Don't just send them off, but click them home a
  screen at a time) folowing the now secured bay-coast, with a bit of 
  luck you should be able to bring the 20 needed people home..

